Cumulative changes
==================

(respective to Free Recode 3.6)

General changes
---------------

+ More charsets are reversible, precise inventory to follow later.

Option changes
--------------

+ Bare :samp:`--list` (:samp:`-l`) should now be written
  :samp:`--list=codings` (:samp:`-lc`).
+ :samp:`--silent` or :samp:`--quiet` (:samp:`-q`) is accepted but ignored.
+ :samp:`--source` (:samp:`-S`) and :samp:`--headers` (:samp:`-h`)
  now require a language.
+ :samp:`--freeze-table` (:samp:`-F`) disappears,
  now a separate maintenance program.
+ :samp:`--find-subsets` (:samp:`-T`) disappears,
  now a separate maintenance program.

Charsets and surfaces
---------------------

+ :code:`Unicode-Escape-X` charset, according to Java documentation.
+ :code:`flat` and :code:`Texinfo` are better connected.
+ :code:`q4` and :code:`QNX-4` as new aliases for :code:`IBM437`.
+ :code:`test7`, :code:`test8`, :code:`test15` and :code:`test16` now
  charsets, not surfaces.

Prior history
-------------

For prior history, see :file:`NEWS` in Free recode.  Both :file:`NEWS`
file will eventually get merged.
